{"id":52964,"date":"2024-01-04T10:08:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-04T04:38:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=52964"},"modified":"2024-01-05T22:40:42","modified_gmt":"2024-01-05T17:10:42","slug":"10-tips-for-decorating-white-walls","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/10-tips-for-decorating-white-walls\/","title":{"rendered":"Magical Makeovers: 10 Tips for Decorating With White Walls"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>White walls are a timeless classic since they can be used for traditional and modern interiors. Learn more on how to decorate them.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>White paint can do wonders for the surroundings that other paint colours can&#8217;t, which makes it a popular choice in today\u2019s age. White walls are an essential part of your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\">home interiors<\/a>, and incorporating them is beneficial because:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>White makes the room look more welcoming, warm and inviting.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It is the ideal backdrop for introducing brighter\/darker colours.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It contributes to creating a sense of spaciousness in the room.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White can be used for both modern &amp; traditional interiors.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It promotes calmness, clarity, purity, innocence, positivity, and balance in the space.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It is practically easy to retouch and clean as there is no fear of fading from scrubbing marks off walls.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>White wall decor ideas create effects:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Personality Effect &#8211;<\/strong> It enhances the ability to immerse your personality into the decorating scheme of your home through creative play with colourful accessories, vibrant throw cushions\/pillows, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Timeless Effect &#8211;<\/strong> It lends a relaxing and uncluttered appeal to the room as it allows \u2018somewhere for your eyes to rest\u2019 between the continued doses of colour and works across all design styles. <strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Gallery Effect &#8211; <\/strong>It bounces natural light from the windows or the artificial lights since white is the most reflective of all the colours. The white ceiling and walls can blend, which makes it harder to distinguish where one ends and the other begins. Hence, it creates an illusion of more vertical space.&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s now read through 10 tips that can help you use your white wall decor optimally and elevate the overall aesthetics of the space:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Install Green Potted Plants to Complement the White Walls\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Connect the serene natural environment to the home interiors by adding some green plants and colourful flowers. They lend elegance with their beautiful leaf shapes and offer cleaner air. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/laminate-wood-flooring-designs\/\">Wooden flooring<\/a> and trims play well with the white walls by adding a rustic dimension.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants.jpg\" alt=\"Decorating white walls by installing green potted plants\" class=\"wp-image-52974\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222750\/decorating-white-walls-with-green-plants-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Green plants bring nature indoors.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use Furniture Pieces to Offset White Wall Decor\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>White walls allow your big spaces to shine as they act as a blank canvas for key furniture pieces like sofa sets and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/different-types-of-tv-units\/\">TV units<\/a> to showcase themselves. They create a captivating drama through their incredible veining and wooden tones like oak, mahogany, cider, teak, etc. Use your showstopper furniture pieces against a white backdrop for simplified gorgeousness.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture.jpg\" alt=\"White walls with colourful furniture like sofa sets and TV units\" class=\"wp-image-52973\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222742\/white-walls-with-colourful-furniture-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Colourful furniture for the win<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Curves Over Angles: White Wall Decor Ideas<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Use curves to introduce softness and elegance into the white-walled space against the non-negotiable angular elements like doors and windows. Coffee centre tables and textiles\/rugs are examples of such rounded shapes. You could also consider using a collection of round or oval mirrors to highlight the room\u2019s subtle aesthetics.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion.jpg\" alt=\"White wall decor by creating a visual illusion to add softness and elegance\" class=\"wp-image-52972\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222735\/white-wall-decor-with-visual-illusion-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Create visual illusions<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">White Wall Art Decor<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Draw the eye up in a white-walled room by hanging large artwork pieces and draperies. The simple logic is that the furniture pieces typically cover the bottom half of the room while the walls and ceiling cover the room&#8217;s middle and upper half, respectively.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor.jpg\" alt=\"White wall decor by hanging large artwork pieces and draperies\" class=\"wp-image-52971\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222728\/white-wall-art-decor-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Abstract art decor for the maximalists<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Mirror for Off-White Wall Decor<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Place a stylish mirror or two against the off-white walls to create a perception of more space while adding a touch of luxury. If the mirror has a coloured or wooden frame, it makes the room come alive. The types of mirrors you can choose from are &#8211; freestanding, sunburst, circular or rectangular mirrors.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror.jpg\" alt=\"Off-white wall decor with a mirror to add a touch of luxury\" class=\"wp-image-52970\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222720\/off-white-wall-decor-with-mirror-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The candlelight adds a soft glow<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">White Walls &amp; Partitions: Ideal for Open-Plan Rooms\u00a0\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have multiple rooms in your home that you can see in one view or have designed it in an open-plan layout, white walls make the space more tranquil and refreshing. Introduce <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/wooden-partition-designs-between-living-room-and-dining-room\/\">wooden partitions <\/a>to distinguish between zones and give you a feeling of positive enclosure and security.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout.jpg\" alt=\"White walls and partitions in an open-plan layout for an elegant look\" class=\"wp-image-52969\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222713\/white-walls-and-partitions-for-open-layout-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Wooden partitions for elegant demarcations<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Lighting Impacts White Wall Decor\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to walls, even white ones, consider the impact of light settings within the space. White paint makes a poor-lit room look large, while it makes big rooms look even larger. Add neutral tones to your home with white colour as the base to create a more layered look. The type of artificial light setting and the number of lights depends upon the size of the space and the vibe you want. You can use a floor light to introduce vertical height or a designer chandelier or sconces to make a bold statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights.jpg\" alt=\"White wall decor with pendant lights to make the room look larger\" class=\"wp-image-52968\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222705\/white-wall-decor-with-pendant-lights-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Pendant lights make the room look large<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Decorate White Walls? With Wallpapers!\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Use wallpaper to accent your white walls and add visual depth and character. Specific design styles pair well, like the white and black brick wall texture (a harmonious blend of past and present), exposed brick wall texture, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/brick-wall-tiles\/\">brick tile wall<\/a> (industrial appeal) and more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers.jpg\" alt=\"White wall decor with accent wallpapers to glam up the room\" class=\"wp-image-52967\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222656\/white-wall-decor-with-accent-wallpapers-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Accent wallpaper glams up this room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Explore trendsetting home interiors to redefine your space\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/20175655\/explore-trendsetting-home-interiors-to-redefine-your-space.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Decorate White Walls in Living Room?\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>White can be used as the main hue or an accent colour, depending on what type of look and feel you want to achieve in the space. Light colour pairing creates a more gentle and subtle appearance, while dark colour pairing creates a striking and dramatic appearance. Use the concept of \u2018layering\u2019 if you are playing around with gradations of white. Sage green, navy blue, light grey, taupe, lavender, black and beige go well with white. They create a balanced and versatile aesthetic.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every colour combination with white produces specific effects on the room\u2019s visuals:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>White and Red &#8211; Warm and passionate look | Softer blush tones\/bold scarlet hues&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Green &#8211; Natural and fresh look | Bold emerald hues\/soft mint greens<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Black &#8211; Elegant and modern look | Classic vibe&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Purple &#8211; Regal and sophisticated look&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Brown &#8211; Earthy and welcoming look&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Pink &#8211; Dreamy and dreamy look&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Blue &#8211; Peaceful and bright look<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>White and Yellow &#8211; Positive and energetic look<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls.jpg\" alt=\"Decorating white walls in the living room with earthy and natural tones\/textures\" class=\"wp-image-52966\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222648\/decorating-living-room-white-walls-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Accentuate the room with earthy and natural tones\/textures to add a splash of colour<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">White Decor Wall With Floating Shelves<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Floating shelves can create themed displays in a room with white walls. They are an incredible space-saver as you can place all the objects you want to see every morning in one fixed place and act as a prominent conversation starter among family members and guests.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves.jpg\" alt=\"White wall decor with floating shelves to create themed displays\" class=\"wp-image-52965\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/05222639\/white-wall-decor-with-floating-shelves-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The floating TV unit against an off-white wall<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wrapping Up<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>All in all, white walls give your home a crisp appearance and a fresh design approach. Consult the interior design experts at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a> if you plan on decorating white walls in your home. Good Luck!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs On Decorating With White Walls<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can white wall decoration be used for both modern and traditional interiors?<\/strong><br>Of course, white wall decoration can be used for both traditional and modern interiors because it is a neutral colour that can easily blend with other colours in the colour wheel.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can white wall art decor be easily combined with other colours &amp; patterns?<\/strong><br>White wall art decor can be easily combined with other patterns and colours. Both combine to create a powerful effect that makes a space feel cosy yet playful. Different materials, like velvet, leather, and woven fabric, add depth and distinctiveness to the furnishings. Textures also don\u2019t necessarily mean only fabrics. Think wall panelling made from wood and painted white. When it comes to the best colour(s) for the wall trim, look to your key furniture pieces for inspiration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can white wall decoration be used to create a Scandinavian or minimalist-inspired look?<\/strong><br>White wall decoration can be used to create a minimalist and Scandinavian-inspired look. Let\u2019s see how:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Minimalist Look<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It features soft colour palettes, expansive spatial plans and clean design lines.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It drives on the principle of \u2018less is more\u2019 and \u2018everything needs a reason and place\u2019.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It includes man-made materials such as lacquered plastics and stainless steel kitchen cabinets.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Scandinavian Look<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It blends soft hues and textures, space-saving and multi-functional furniture.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It focuses on cosiness and warmth yet uncluttered appearance or the Hygge principle in the home interiors.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It pairs well with greys, pastels and some nature\/wood-inspired colours.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>It includes organic materials such as woven baskets, hemp\/cotton rugs and standard\/curved wooden chairs.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Can you use a two-tone approach for white walls?<\/strong><br>You can definitely create a two-tone approach. Use white on the upper half of the walls and a contrasting colour on the lower half for a modern and contemporary look.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n       